ttttcclloossee() -- Terminal-Device Routine

#iinncclluuddee <ssyyss/ttttyy.hh>
vvooiidd
ttttcclloossee(_t_p)
TTTTYY *_t_p;

ttttcclloossee() is  called by  a terminal  device driver on  the last  close.  It
waits for  pending output  to be  sent, then flushes  input and  resets the
internal state information for the given tty.

